Check your database (log into MySQL and run SHOW TABLES;)
You should see a special table like _migrations (or similar) that tracks which migrations ran.

Add real schema changes
If your app needs tables (like users, claims, etc.), you’ll put those db.createTable(...) statements inside the migration file.

Run new migrations
Whenever you want to evolve your schema, just run:

npx db-migrate create add-users-table --sql-file -e dev --config database.json


Then edit that new migration file with your schema changes, and apply with:

npx db-migrate up -e dev --config database.json

To get those running go to powershell
